						               													<description>More challenges from the Destreza Mental game.  This is a stand alone version - it does not need the original game to be played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a competitive game between 2 and 6 players. On their turn, each player must perform one of the 8 challenges, in a time of one minute. If he succeeds, he wins the token for that challenge. Whoever gets the 8 different tokens wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 8 challenges are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Memory: find out which is the missing province.&amp;#10;     Language: form a sentence with seven letters.&amp;#10;     Visuospatial: order mamushkas from largest to smallest.&amp;#10;     Calculation: do a mathematical calculation.&amp;#10;     Multitasking: place domino cards alternating the higher and lower numbers.&amp;#10;     Logic: place the twelve cards without touching consecutive cards.&amp;#10;     Inhibition: place cards but only one of its three characteristics matches.&amp;#10;     Social cognition: discover where the other player hides a card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
